    "claim": "The branch-free Eye Shredder tape reproduces the documented cursor breakout as the exact position-113 write in a bounded original-layout dName model, and Aurora observes the resulting raw XF/BP channel-count mismatch at a real draw boundary before controllable gameplay is reached.",
    "required_setup": [
      "Boot the GCN NTSC-U game from a clean automation state with no existing save.",
      "Use the cursor_breakout_shadow fidelity profile and the eye-shredder semantic oracle.",
      "Replay the checked absolute 650-frame tape with physical controller input disconnected.",
      "Retain the authenticated observation, gameplay trace, native timing, name-entry trace, and oracle result."
    ],
    "fidelity_limitations": [
      "The retail write is applied to a bounded original-layout shadow model; native host memory is never accessed out of bounds and the host dName object is not claimed to occupy its GameCube address.",
      "Aurora preserves the command multiplicity and diagnoses the exact XF/BP mismatch, but the magenta/cyan diagnostic is not a pixel-accurate reproduction of the console triangular/rainbow artifact.",
      "The native-port claim proves the modeled corruption signature and renderer-state consequence only; it does not prove arbitrary cursor-breakout writes or original-console rasterization."
    ],
